FBIS3-56968 "drsov015_a_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS `Real Fears' About Ukranian Nuclear Arms Voiced PM2001092994 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 2020 GMT 18 Jan 94 PM2001092994 Moscow Russian Television Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Announcer-read report from the "Vesti" newscast] [Text] A press conference on the military-political aspects of the agreement between the Russian, U.S., and Ukrainian presidents was held at the Defense Ministry today. Leading Russian nuclear disarmament specialists expressed real fears about the condition of the Ukrainian nuclear arsenal. The stockpiles are overloaded, the personnel are poorly trained, and proper servicing is not carried out. Given this situation, Russian plants are prepared to dismantle all Ukrainian warheads within two years. The ball is now in the Ukrainian leadership's court. [Video shows warships in harbor, under construction]
